<div class="quotetitle">Grumskiz wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />From what I know the emphasis bits cannot be combined on the NES, so checkboxes could confuse people into thinking that this can be done.<br /></div><br /><br />They can. In fact, some developers have their games set <span style="text-decoration: underline">all</span> the emphasis bits -- this makes the colors quite a bit darker.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Of course when Monochrome Mode is selected the drop down menu for the color emphasis needs to be inactive.<br /></div><br /><br />They don't. Quoting the wiki's &quot;PPU registers&quot; page, <br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />In either case, the tint bits are applied after grayscale, which means they still tint the gray image.<br /></div><br /><br />-- that is, the tint bits can be enabled (and will make sense) even in grayscale mode.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5140">usr_share</a> — Tue Aug 21, 2012 8:16 am</p><hr />
